snippet: The Proton-M rocket, which was ferrying a telecommunications satellite, crashed minutes after launch on Saturday, Russian news agencies reported.
abstract: Russian-made rocket carrying Mexican telecommunications satellite crashes in eastern Siberia after taking off from Kazakhstan.

byline.contributor: Randal C. Archibold contributed reporting from Mexico City.

lead_paragraph: The Proton-M rocket, which was ferrying a telecommunications satellite, crashed minutes after launch on Saturday, Russian news agencies reported.

headline.main: Russian Rocket Carrying Mexican Satellite Is Said to Crash in Siberia
headline.print_headline: Russian Rocket and Mexican Satellite Crash in Siberia
